---
description: Design system token and component rules — enforced on all component files
globs: src/components/**/*
alwaysApply: false
---

## Token Approach
Approach A — inline token refs. No Tailwind arbitrary values.

## Color Rules
- Use tokens from `design-system.tsx` only — never raw hex values in component files
- Semantic color tokens: `colors.bg0`–`colors.bg4` for backgrounds, `colors.t0`–`colors.t3` for text, `colors.teal` / `colors.amber` / `colors.risk` for semantic states
- Pain score color: always use `painColor(score)` helper from `design-system.tsx` — never inline pain color logic
- Never use `colors.teal` as a background fill on large surfaces — teal is accent only
- `colors.bgInverse` is for CTA button fills and callout backgrounds only

## Spacing Rules
- Spacing tokens from `design-system.tsx`: `spacing[4]`, `spacing[8]`, `spacing[12]`, etc.
- Never raw pixel values in style props — no `padding: '13px'`, `gap: '7px'`
- Touch targets: `touchTarget.lg` (46px) for standard buttons, `touchTarget.xl` (52px) for onboarding/paywall CTAs only, `touchTarget.sm` (32px) for icon buttons

## Typography Rules
- Font families: `typography.fontPrimary` (Be Vietnam Pro), `typography.fontDisplay` (Figtree), `typography.fontMono` (DM Mono)
- Font size tokens: `typography.size09` through `typography.size26` — never raw rem or px values
- Font weight tokens: `typography.w400` through `typography.w800` — never raw numbers

## Border and Radius Rules
- All borders: `1px solid ${colors.border}` — never vary border width or colour except active/error states
- Active border: `1.5px solid ${colors.t0}` for selected rows, `1.5px solid ${colors.risk}` for error states
- Radius tokens: `radius.r4` through `radius.full` — never raw values like `borderRadius: '5px'`
- No drop shadows — depth via background color steps only (`bg0` → `bg1` → `bg2` → `bg3` → `bg4`)
- No gradients on any surface

## Component Rules
- Use exported components from `design-system.tsx` — check the Component → Screen Registry (Section 12) before creating any new component
- Never create a one-off component in a screen file if an equivalent exists in `design-system.tsx`
- Every interactive component must implement all applicable states: default / loading / error / empty / disabled
- Loading state: use `SkeletonBlock` or `SkeletonText` — never return null or hide the container
- Empty state: use `EmptyState` component — never blank space
- Error state: use `ErrorBanner` component — never raw text

## Animation Rules
- Animation tokens only: `animation.micro` (120ms), `animation.standard` (200ms), `animation.progress` (700ms with 400ms delay)
- No spring physics, no bounce, no scale > 2%
- Typing indicator: always `TypingIndicator` component — 800ms minimum display even if response arrives faster
- Progress bar fill: always 400ms delay after mount, 700ms fill — use `ProgressBar` with `delay={400}` prop
